The All Progressives Congress (APC) is set to officially unveil its 2023 vice presidential candidate, Kashim Shettima. The presidential standard bearer, Bola Tinubu earlier announced Shettima as his running mate. The former Borno governor and Senator will be presented to the Nigerian public on Wednesday. APC National Organising Secretary, Sulaiman Argungu made this known in a statement on Tuesday. The event will take place at the Shehu Musa Yar’Adua Centre, Abuja. The party invited members of the National Executive Committee (NEC), Progressives Governors’ Forum, APC Caucus in the National Assembly, Federal Executive Council (FEC) and Diplomatic Corps. Others are presidential aspirants at the June 2022 Special National Convention, APC State Chairmen, Secretaries and Organising Secretaries.